<subSubSection pageId="303" pageNumber="304" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="303" pageNumber="304">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="303" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviatus">Dyschirius abbreviatus</taxonomicName>
Putzeys, 1846 [January]: 12. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="«Texas»">&quot;Texas&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Putzeys 1861: 71), restricted to &quot;Galveston [Galveston County]&quot; by Putzeys (1867b: 51). Holotype [by monotypy] in MHNP (collection Chaudoir). Note. Putzeys (1846: 13) originally gave 
<normalizedToken originalValue="«Yucatan»">&quot;Yucatan&quot;</normalizedToken>
as type locality but changed it to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="«Texas»">&quot;Texas&quot;</normalizedToken>
later (Putzeys 1861: 71). This species is a senior primary homonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="303" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="303" pageNumber="304">Dyschirius abbreviatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1846 [June].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="303" pageNumber="304" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="303" pageNumber="304">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="303" pageNumber="304">This species inhabits the Coastal Plain ranging from the coast of southern North Carolina (Brunswick County, Ken Karns pers. comm. 2009) to southern Florida (Nichols 1988b: Fig. 5-5; Peck and Thomas 1998: 17), west to southeastern Texas (Putzeys 1867b: 51).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="303" pageNumber="304" type="records">
<paragraph pageId="303" pageNumber="304">Records.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="303" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="303" pageNumber="304">USA</emphasis>
: AL, FL, GA, LA, MS, NC, TX
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="303" pageNumber="304" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="303" pageNumber="304">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="303" pageNumber="304">
According to Whitehead (1970: 185), members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kult" authorityYear="1950" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="303" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darlingtoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="303" pageNumber="304">Dyschirius darlingtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kult, 1950 from Mexico are probably conspecific with those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="303" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="303" pageNumber="304">Dyschirius abbreviatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
